01:23:14,494 --> 01:23:18,332
Y aunque la vida me cueste, Llorona

1065
01:23:18,498 --> 01:23:21,543
No dejaré de quererte

1066
01:23:21,919 --> 01:23:25,339
-Let go of me!
-Y aunque la vida me cueste, Llorona

1067
01:23:25,881 --> 01:23:28,884
No dejaré de quererte

1068
01:23:29,051 --> 01:23:32,596
No dejaré de quererte

1069
01:23:32,763 --> 01:23:37,100
No dejaré de quererte

1070
01:23:37,809 --> 01:23:40,270
Ay, ay, ay

1071
01:23:49,613 --> 01:23:51,532
I forgot what that felt like.

1072
01:23:51,698 --> 01:23:54,076
You still got it.

1073
01:24:00,457 --> 01:24:03,168
Miguel, I give you my blessing.

1074
01:24:04,795 --> 01:24:10,342
To go home, to put up our photos
and to never--

1075
01:24:10,509 --> 01:24:12,636
Never play music again.

1076
01:24:13,971 --> 01:24:18,517
To never forget
how much your family loves you.

1077
01:24:21,186 --> 01:24:22,521
You're going home.

1078
01:24:26,316 --> 01:24:28,235
You're not going anywhere.

1079
01:24:29,695 --> 01:24:30,696
Imelda!

1080
01:24:31,029 --> 01:24:36,159
Stay back! Stay back!
All of you, stay back. Not one more step.

1081
01:24:38,161 --> 01:24:39,413
Dante!

1082
01:24:41,039 --> 01:24:45,252
Ernesto, stop! Leave the boy alone.

1083
01:24:45,419 --> 01:24:49,590
I've worked too hard, Héctor.
Too hard to let him destroy everything.

1084
01:24:49,756 --> 01:24:51,675
He's a living child, Ernesto.

1085
01:24:51,842 --> 01:24:53,177
He's a threat!

1086
01:24:53,343 --> 01:24:56,972
You think I'd let him go back
to the Land of the Living with your photo?

1087
01:24:57,139 --> 01:25:00,058
To keep your memory alive? No.

1088
01:25:00,225 --> 01:25:02,936
-You're a coward!
-I am Ernesto de la Cruz.

1089
01:25:03,103 --> 01:25:04,813
The greatest musician of all time!

1090
01:25:04,938 --> 01:25:06,690
Héctor's the real musician.

1091
01:25:06,773 --> 01:25:09,234
You're just the guy who murdered him
and stole his songs!

1092
01:25:09,318 --> 01:25:10,319
Murdered?

1093
01:25:10,819 --> 01:25:14,364
I am the one who's willing to do
what it takes to seize my moment.

1094
01:25:15,032 --> 01:25:16,533
Whatever it takes.

1095
01:25:19,161 --> 01:25:20,162
No!

1096
01:25:22,372 --> 01:25:23,624
Miguel!

1097
01:25:24,458 --> 01:25:27,711
Apologies, old friend.
But the show must go on.

1098
01:26:11,004 --> 01:26:12,714
Please, please, mi familia.

1099
01:26:12,881 --> 01:26:14,341
Murderer!

1100
01:26:15,008 --> 01:26:17,344
Orchestra. A-one, a-two, a-one--

1101
01:26:20,013 --> 01:26:23,851
Remember me
Though I have to s-- Hey!

1102
01:26:25,602 --> 01:26:26,603
Look!

1103
01:26:47,374 --> 01:26:48,625
Nice kitty.

1104
01:26:52,880 --> 01:26:57,384
Put me down! No, please! I beg of you!
Stop! Stop! No!

1105
01:27:06,101 --> 01:27:07,477
No! No!

1106
01:27:19,448 --> 01:27:20,532
What did I miss?

1107
01:27:20,616 --> 01:27:22,159
Good boy, Dante!

1108
01:27:22,242 --> 01:27:23,243
Miguel!

1109
01:27:25,245 --> 01:27:29,499
Héctor! The photo... I lost it!

1110
01:27:29,666 --> 01:27:31,668
It's okay, mijo. It's o--

1111
01:27:32,586 --> 01:27:35,088
Héctor! Héctor?

1112
01:27:36,340 --> 01:27:37,341
Coco.

1113
01:27:37,508 --> 01:27:39,927
No! We can still find the photo.

1114
01:27:40,093 --> 01:27:41,595
Miguel, it's almost sunrise.

1115
01:27:42,930 --> 01:27:44,473
No, no. I can't leave you.

1116
01:27:44,640 --> 01:27:49,102
I promised I'd put your photo up.
I promised you'd see Coco.

1117
01:27:49,269 --> 01:27:51,355
We're both out of time, mijo.

1118
01:27:52,689 --> 01:27:55,859
Oh no! No! She can't forget you!

1119
01:27:56,026 --> 01:27:59,863
I just wanted her to know
that I loved her.

1120
01:28:01,198 --> 01:28:04,284
-Héctor!
-You have our blessing, Miguel.

1121
01:28:04,952 --> 01:28:06,703
No conditions.

1122
01:28:07,371 --> 01:28:10,123
No! Papá Héctor, please!

1123
01:28:14,336 --> 01:28:15,379
No!

1124
01:28:16,713 --> 01:28:20,801
-Go home.
-I promise I won't let Coco forget you!

1125
01:28:48,036 --> 01:28:49,329
There he is!

1126
01:28:50,706 --> 01:28:52,416
Miguel! Stop!

1127
01:28:57,754 --> 01:29:00,883
-Where have you been?
-I need to see Mamá Coco, please.

1128
01:29:01,049 --> 01:29:03,510
What are you doing with that--
Give it to me!

1129
01:29:04,178 --> 01:29:07,848
Miguel, stop! Miguel! Miguel!

1130
01:29:09,850 --> 01:29:13,562
Mamá Coco? Can you hear me? It's Miguel.

1131
01:29:14,229 --> 01:29:17,733
I saw your papá. Remember? Papá?

1132
01:29:19,067 --> 01:29:24,573
Please! If you forget him,
he'll be gone. Forever.

1133
01:29:25,365 --> 01:29:26,783
Miguel, open this door!

1134
01:29:26,950 --> 01:29:30,954
Here. This was his guitar, right?
He used to play it to you?

1135
01:29:33,916 --> 01:29:39,880
See? There he is! Papá! Remember? Papá?

1136
01:29:43,550 --> 01:29:47,304
-Miguel!
-Mamá Coco, please! Don't forget him.

1137
01:29:54,061 --> 01:29:57,231
What are you doing to that poor woman?
It's okay, Mamita. It's okay.

1138
01:29:57,397 --> 01:29:58,649
What's gotten into you?

1139
01:30:05,322 --> 01:30:06,990
I thought I'd lost you, Miguel.

1140
01:30:07,157 --> 01:30:08,575
I'm sorry, Papá.

1141
01:30:08,742 --> 01:30:11,787
We're all together now.
That's what matters.

1142
01:30:12,996 --> 01:30:13,997
Not all of us.

1143
01:30:14,164 --> 01:30:19,336
It's okay, Mamita.
Miguel, you apologize to your Mamá Coco.

1144
01:30:22,673 --> 01:30:24,091
Mamá Coco?

1145
01:30:29,137 --> 01:30:30,973
Well? Apologize!

1146
01:30:34,977 --> 01:30:40,774
Mamá Coco?
Your papá, he wanted you to have this.

1147
01:30:42,776 --> 01:30:44,486
Mamá, wait!

1148
01:30:44,653 --> 01:30:48,490
Remember me

1149
01:30:49,825 --> 01:30:52,619
Though I have to say goodbye

1150
01:30:52,786 --> 01:30:55,455
Remember me

1151
01:30:56,123 --> 01:30:58,709
Don't let it make you cry

1152
01:30:58,876 --> 01:31:02,462
For even if I'm far away

1153
01:31:02,629 --> 01:31:08,468
I hold you in my heart
I sing a secret song to you

1154
01:31:08,635 --> 01:31:11,805
Each night we are apart

1155
01:31:12,472 --> 01:31:15,809
Remember me

1156
01:31:16,476 --> 01:31:19,771
Though I have to travel far

1157
01:31:20,439 --> 01:31:22,524
Remember me

1158
01:31:23,192 --> 01:31:26,820
Each time you hear a sad guitar

1159
01:31:28,155 --> 01:31:33,619
Know that I'm with you
The only way that I can be

1160
01:31:35,621 --> 01:31:39,875
Until you're in my arms again

1161
01:31:41,877 --> 01:31:48,342
Remember me

1162
01:31:55,182 --> 01:31:58,644
Elena? What's wrong, mija?

1163
01:31:59,311 --> 01:32:02,981
Nothing, Mamá. Nothing at all.

1164
01:32:04,316 --> 01:32:07,694
My papá used to sing me that song.

1165
01:32:08,362 --> 01:32:10,405
He loved you, Mamá Coco.

1166
01:32:11,073 --> 01:32:14,701
Your papá loved you so much.

1167
01:32:33,345 --> 01:32:36,682
I kept his letters.

1168
01:32:37,349 --> 01:32:41,562
Poems he wrote me. And...

1169
01:33:01,081 --> 01:33:03,709
Papá was a musician.

1170
01:33:04,376 --> 01:33:06,545
When I was a little girl...

1171
01:33:08,839 --> 01:33:12,092
he and Mamá
would sing such beautiful songs.

1172
01:33:18,265 --> 01:33:20,726
ONE YEAR LATER

1173
01:33:21,560 --> 01:33:24,813
Remember Me

1174
01:33:24,980 --> 01:33:28,859
And right over here,
one of Santa Cecilia's greatest treasures.

1175
01:33:29,109 --> 01:33:32,821
The home of the esteemed song writer,
Héctor Rivera.

1176
01:33:33,488 --> 01:33:35,407
The letters Héctor wrote home

1177
01:33:35,490 --> 01:33:37,117
for his daughter, Coco,
contain the lyrics...

1178
01:33:37,284 --> 01:33:40,787
for all of your favorite songs.
Not just Remember Me.

1179
01:33:44,791 --> 01:33:46,960
And that man is your Papá Julio.

1180
01:33:47,127 --> 01:33:50,255
And there's Tía Rosita
and your Tía Victoria.

1181
01:33:50,422 --> 01:33:53,300
And those two are Oscar and Felipe.

1182
01:33:53,967 --> 01:33:56,345
These aren't just old pictures,
they're our family...

1183
01:33:56,512 --> 01:33:58,639
and they're counting on us
to remember them.

1184
01:34:16,490 --> 01:34:21,662
Say that I'm crazy or call me a fool

1185
01:34:26,041 --> 01:34:27,751
Enjoy your visit, Héctor.

1186
01:34:29,628 --> 01:34:32,506
But last night it seemed that
I dreamed about you

1187
01:34:35,843 --> 01:34:38,720
-Papá!
-Coco!

1188
01:34:38,929 --> 01:34:43,600
When I opened my mouth
what came out was a song

1189
01:34:43,767 --> 01:34:49,523
And you know every word
and we all sang along

1190
01:34:53,026 --> 01:34:56,738
To a melody played
on the strings of our souls

1191
